24/10/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Office of the High Representative (OHR) welcomed BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic's statement Friday (22 October) that the government was ready to freeze the assets of indicted war criminals' assets, as the EU has requested.
Later the same day, the Republika Srpska (RS) government spokesman Goran Radivojac said the RS cabinet would adopt the measure at an entity level.
In neighbouring Croatia, the government also reportedly decided in favour of Brussels' request.
Also on Friday, BiH Presidency Chairman Sulejman Tihic met with US Ambassador to BiH Douglas McElhaney.
Aftewards, Tihic said the two countries agreed that the United States would retain the Orao military base in Tuzla after SFOR completes its mandate in December.
He also said Washington supports a BiH offer to deploy a demining unit in Iraq.
(Nezavisne novine - 23/10/04;
HIC Centre, HINA, Fena, PBS BiH, Pincom.info, Reuters - 22/10/04)
